<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-166-088 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 625 704</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Sources  May 1991 v2 n5 p62(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Keeping your floppy drives clean. (Trackmate America Corp.'sTrackmate)(Forum)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Colossi, Dawn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Trackmate America Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   TrackMate (Utility program) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Floppy DiskDisk DrivesUtility ProgramsMaintenanceDiagnostic Assessment.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>KEEPING YOUR FLOPPY DRIVES CLEAN Floppy disk drives are vulnerable to dustand dirt because they're open to the outside world.andP;  Dirt can make your driveslow down.andP;  Or worse, cause you to lose important data.andP;  Trackmate byTrackmate America Corp. (Los Gatos, CA, 408-356-0795) can solve your floppydrive cleaning needs.andM;You first run the package's diagnostic software, which assesses your drive'supper and lower heads' ability to correctly read and write data.andP;  It thenmeasures your drive's speed to give you the percent variation from the idealspeed, and determines if the drive passes or fails.andP;  If it fails, the programrecommends you clean the drive.andP;  To do this, you fill Trackmate's specialcleaning disk with the included isopropyl alcohol, using an instrument thatlooks like a thick felt-tipped pen.andP;  The diagnostics program will prompt youto insert the disk and will then begin the cleaning process, which typicallytakes 30 seconds.andP;  The company suggests checking your floppy drive once aweek.andP;  Trackmate is good for up to 52 cleanings and is available for both5.25-and 3.5-inch disk drives.andP;  List price is $34.95 for one drive size or$44.l95 for both drive sizes.andP;  Mail-order prices are $30 and $39respectively.andO;</TEXT></DOC>